mod1.mod_description: VisualV Remastered is a captivating modification for Grand Theft Auto V Legacy that revitalizes the game's urban landscape with a fresh, atmospheric overhaul. As depicted in the image, this mod introduces a vibrant nighttime cityscape featuring illuminated buildings, bustling streets, and a starry sky, creating a lively yet serene ambiance. With enhanced lighting, detailed architecture, and a modern aesthetic, Project: Revive breathes new life into Los Santos, offering players an immersive and visually striking experience that elevates the game's original environment.

mod2.mod_description: Step back into neon-soaked nights and pastel-sunset streets with the “Vice City visuals” remake of VisualV for Grand Theft Auto V: a full overhaul that re-tones time of day, weather, lighting and colour grading to capture that iconic 1980s Miami-vice aesthetic. Expect crisp skies, saturated twilight hues, bold reflections, sharper shadows and a cinematic glow that turns Los Santos into a retro-dreamboard of palm trees, neon signs and midnight drives. Compatible with the original VisualV base, this legacy version channels classic vibes while retaining top-tier visual fidelity.

mod_1766594766993.mod_description: Sakura Vibe Graphics is a stylized visual overhaul that bathes Los Santos in a soft, dreamy aesthetic. Perfect for players seeking a "girly" or high-fashion look, this mod features vibrant pink and purple color grading, cherry blossom-inspired foliage, and a matching custom pink HUD and minimap. Transform your game into a serene, neon-pastel paradise with cinematic lighting that makes every sunset feel like a dream.

mod_1766595104176.mod_description: Sakura Vibe Graphics ENB is the high-performance, ultra-demanding version of our stylized graphics pack. Built for elite setups, it takes the dreamy aesthetic to the next level with advanced ray-traced reflections, deeper ambient occlusion, and enhanced light bloom. Experience the ultimate pink-toned paradise with maximum visual fidelity and cinematic depth that truly brings the "Sakura" world to life.

mod16.mod_description: VisualV Winter: Graphics Overhaul is the specialized seasonal component for the acclaimed VisualV graphics modification. It provides a comprehensive overhaul of Los Santos' visual fidelity, re-tuning the entire atmosphere to perfectly complement a winter environment; this mod fundamentally adjusts the game's core rendering to create an authentic winter mood, featuring Rewritten Weather cycles simulating a cold, overcast climate, eliminating the harsh California sun in favor of soft, diffused light. Atmospheric Realism is enhanced through volumetric fog, resulting in a dramatic, cold haze over the city; Lighting Correction adjusts tone mapping to produce cooler, more muted colors; and Enhanced Draw Distance allows the winter landscape to appear vast and richly detailed, making this mod essential for achieving the most realistic and atmospheric winter playthrough in GTA V.

mod25.mod_description: Real Graphics is a photo-realistic graphics mod for GTA V that delivers a cinematic, highly immersive look. It features a complete overhaul of the lighting, weather, and reflections to achieve stunning visual fidelity in Los Santos, making the world appear incredibly realistic, especially during dawn, dusk, and night.

mod26.mod_description: Real Graphics ENB is a photo-realistic graphics mod for GTA V that delivers a cinematic, highly immersive look. It features a complete overhaul of the lighting, weather, and reflections to achieve stunning visual fidelity in Los Santos, making the world appear incredibly realistic, especially during dawn, dusk, and night. The ENB version consumes more FPS than the normal one. Not recommended for Low-End PCs.

mod_1767304400393.mod_description: Project Realism Lite is a standalone graphics mod for GTA V Legacy designed to be suitable for any PC. It delivers a complete visual overhaul with enhanced lighting and realistic textures while maintaining high performance. You can easily customize your visuals by pressing the Insert key to open the Reshade menu.

mod_1767304634209.mod_description: Project Realism Pro is a premium graphics mod designed exclusively for high-end PCs, pushing the boundaries of realism in GTA V Legacy. It features advanced lighting, ultra-detailed textures, and superior post-processing for a truly cinematic experience. Use the Insert key to access the Reshade menu and F10 to open the ENB settings for total visual control.

mod_1766587608175.mod_description: RealHood Graphics is our most elite and demanding visual overhaul, designed for high-end setups that crave total immersion. This pack pushes GTA V to its absolute limit with ultra-realistic wet road reflections, cinematic lighting, and gritty atmosphere, delivering a true next-gen experience.

mod3.mod_description:
IMPORTANT! Make sure all your GTA V graphics settings are on the lowest possible!

VenxPvP Graphics is a highly optimized graphical mod designed to give you a significant FPS boost without sacrificing too much visual clarity.

By meticulously adjusting shadows, reflections, particle effects, and more, this mod strips away unnecessary visual overhead to ensure your frame rate remains high and stable, which is absolutely critical for fluid, responsive PvP gameplay.

mod20.mod_description: This component focuses on the game's environment and global lighting. It replaces the default sky and weather textures, typically giving the sky a striking deep purple, pink, or magenta hue and adjusting the overall atmosphere to be moodier and more saturated. This mod unifies the whole Tuffy aesthetic across the game world, ensuring the sky matches the custom HUD and effects.

mod21.mod_description: The Carefree Redux mod is a comprehensive visual modification designed to completely re-envision the atmosphere and lighting of Grand Theft Auto V, moving it toward a more moody, cinematic, and high-fidelity aesthetic that is often favored for roleplay or video production.

mod_1766438037976.mod_description: Gucci Redux is a sleek GTA visual overhaul featuring high-fidelity graphics, a clean white minimap design, and sharp white gun tracers for a modern, tactical look. Experience Los Santos with cinematic lighting and a minimalist aesthetic.

mod15.mod_description:
December Update: Added various christmas-themed mapping mods such as wreath, custom christmas trees, garlands, snowmen and more. Removed the frozen lake.

This mod completely transforms the atmosphere of Los Santos for the holidays. It's an immersive seasonal mapping overhaul that replaces standard streetlights across the map with festive Christmas streetlights. Additionally, it brings extensive Christmas mapping, adding props, decorations, and seasonal visuals throughout Los Santos.

mod4.mod_description: LA Roads Remastered gives Los Santos a complete street-level makeover, replacing outdated textures with ultra-detailed, high-definition asphalt, brick intersections, and authentic Los Angeles-style lane markings. Expect crisp road surfaces, realistic wear patterns, and vibrant urban detailing that make the city feel freshly paved and alive. Perfect for players chasing realism without sacrificing performance, this remaster blends seamlessly with other visual mods for a clean, modern aesthetic.

mod_1767744828437.mod_description: Monaco Roads is a high-quality texture mod for GTA 5 and FiveM that replaces the default Los Santos road surfaces with premium, clean asphalt inspired by European streets. It covers approximately 95% of the game map, providing sharp 4K textures, improved normal maps for realistic depth, and high-fidelity LODs (Level of Detail) to ensure the roads look crisp even from a distance. This mod is widely used in roleplay and cinematic setups to give the city a more modern, "first-world" aesthetic compared to the original weathered textures.

mod5.mod_description: Europe Roads transforms Los Santos with authentic European-style road textures, markings, and asphalt patterns. From crisp lane dividers to realistic tarmac wear, it brings a continental vibe to every drive—perfect for players who want Los Santos to feel more like Paris than Pacific Coast Highway.

mod6.mod_description: LS: Real Locations brings the real-world landmarks and iconic storefronts of Los Santos into razor-sharp focus. This mod replaces generic generic-store facades with recognizable brands and textures, repositions and redesigns points of interest to more faithfully reflect their real-life counterparts, and altogether gives the city a layer of authenticity that doesn’t feel like just another flashy skin. Ideal for players who want immersion over spectacle.

mod7.mod_description: Give every cash machine in Los Santos a fresh facelift and deeper immersion with ATMs Reimagined. The mod replaces generic ATM props with high-detail models, updated textures, realistic bank branding, lighting effects and subtle sound cues, turning each withdrawal point into a believable part of the urban landscape rather than a bland static sign. Perfect for players who want the little details to pop while they’re cruising through the city.

mod8.mod_description: Billboards Reimagined is the essential visual mod for your GTA V Legacy experience. This modification replaces all the original, vanilla billboards and advertisements across Los Santos and Blaine County with a meticulously curated selection of real-life brand billboards.

mod_1767713872368.mod_description: Faces Remastered is a high-definition overhaul for GTA V that replaces vanilla character textures with realistic, high-fidelity skin shaders and detailed facial features. It enhances pores, eyes, and hair rendering to bring NPC and player models up to modern graphical standards, making them look significantly more lifelike for roleplay and cinematics.

mod9.mod_description: Face and Body Improvements overhauls character models with refined facial textures, enhanced skin detail, and subtle anatomical updates for both male and female characters. Expect sharper features, realistic complexion tones, visible muscle definition, and reimagined body mapping that modernizes GTA V’s character visuals without breaking immersion. It’s a tasteful evolution of the game’s look—more lifelike, less plastic.

mod_1767305400952.mod_description: Transform Los Santos into a serene, blooming landscape with the Sakura Trees vegetation mod. This standalone graphics enhancement replaces standard trees with vibrant cherry blossoms, adding a unique and picturesque aesthetic to the world.

mod_1767305812060.mod_description: Elevate your environment with the 4K Vegetation Mod, a comprehensive graphics overhaul that replaces all flora in Los Santos and Blaine County with high-resolution textures. This mod completely reworks trees, palms, bushes, coniferous trees, and fine ground foliage for incredible detail. It features a custom LOD (Level of Detail) system to balance the performance impact and transforms Sandy Shores into a lush, green landscape.

mod23.mod_description:
Important! To make this mod work, you have to go to graphics settings, and turn the Grass Quality to normal or lowest possible! 

This mod removes grass and vegetation, but not tree leaves. This mod is considered legal on servers like B-hood and it's safe to use.

mod24.mod_description:
Uncompatible with GTA V purchased on Rockstar Games Launcher.

Install this with the No Vegetation (Rockstar) in order to fully remove vegetation. This mod removes the leaves, grass, small bushes and small trees. This mod is considered legal on servers like B-hood and it's safe to use.

mod10.mod_description: Winter Minimap Animated adds a frosty twist to your HUD with icy blue health and armor bars, animated indicator text, and gentle snowflakes that fall when you take damage. A small detail that makes every firefight feel like a snowstorm.

mod11.mod_description: Get rid of the clutter! This mod delivers a super clean, minimalist HUD for your game. It replaces the standard radar with a sleek, monochrome minimap showing only essential routes, and simplifies your Health and Armor into small, crisp indicators.

mod13.mod_description: This mod is a focused quality-of-life and aesthetic enhancement for combat. It reskins the Health and Armor bars to a high-contrast pink/magenta color. Crucially, the mod implements a dynamic text display that instantly flashes the player's exact numerical Health Points (HP) when damage is taken, providing immediate and precise combat feedback.

mod14.mod_description: This mod is a focused quality-of-life and aesthetic enhancement for combat. It reskins the Health and Armor bars to a high-contrast pink/magenta color. Crucially, the mod implements a dynamic text display that instantly flashes the player's exact numerical Health Points (HP) when damage is taken, providing immediate and precise combat feedback.

mod17.mod_description:
The Minimap | Spectral mod replaces the standard minimap with a sleek, high-contrast, black-and-white or dark-themed visual design, setting it apart from the vanilla game.

Its core feature is a dynamic spectral damage indicator. When the player takes damage, the minimap itself visually reacts by displaying a glitchy, shimmering, or "spectral" effect (often glowing bright colors like purple or cyan). This provides a distinct and dramatic visual cue for incoming damage and declining health, making combat feel more intense while maintaining a unique, futuristic aesthetic for the HUD.

mod18.mod_description:
This mod is a complete artistic overhaul of the in-game minimap, transforming the utilitarian navigation tool into a bold, themed aesthetic piece.

It replaces the standard road layout and colors with a highly customized look, primarily using shades of pink, black, and gray. The most prominent feature is the overlay of "tuff" or feminine graphics—such as hearts, stylized text (like the "I love who I want" seen in the heart), and kiss-mark icons—giving the radar a distinct, rebellious, and highly personalized "girly-grunge" or "bubblegum-punk" visual vibe. It's a purely cosmetic mod for players who want a dramatically different and visually striking interface.

mod27.mod_description: Minimap | Zoom 0.25x, showing a large area of the surroundings.

mod28.mod_description: Minimap | Zoom 0.50x, offering a good balance of detail and area coverage.

mod29.mod_description: Minimap | Zoom 0.75x, slightly wider than the default.

mod30.mod_description: Minimap | Zoom 1.0x, the standard close-in perspective.

mod19.mod_description:
This mod is the cosmetic component that visually triggers when the player successfully lands a hit on an enemy.

It replaces the standard, subtle particle effect of bullet or impact hits with a dramatic, stylized visual burst. Following the Tuffy aesthetic (pink, rebellious), the mod makes enemies visibly explode into a cloud of pink and white crosses (or similar "girly-punk" icons) upon taking damage. It's a fun, over-the-top, and highly noticeable change to combat feedback.

mod12.mod_description:
Elevate your aim and dominate in player-versus-player combat with the Plus Crosshair mod! This essential visual enhancement replaces your default in-game reticle with a sharp, classic plus-sign crosshair. Designed for maximum clarity and precision, it gives you a distinct and stable focal point, crucial for landing those critical shots.

Ideal for PvP: Gain an edge in firefights with a clear, unambiguous crosshair that helps you track targets and make every shot count.
